Honestly {{champion:1}}  delivers on the theme of assassination better than {{champion:91}}

Due to her lack of mobility, she can't just run straight at her target try to stab them in the face. She needs to be sneaky, flanking her target and waiting for their escape routes to be cut off before closing for the kill.

...

Or she just goes {{item:3092}} {{summoner:4}} {{item:3152}} and jumps at your face like some drunken brozerker {{champion:2}}

And their method for getting to the backline is identical to {{champion:39}} {{champion:59}} {{champion:24}} 
Charge your opponent head on and kill them.

Flavor wise, how is charging your opponent head on like an assassin trying to sneak up on their prey?
